Introduction¶

This dataset contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), including user ratings and revenue, etc. the original datset can be downloaded from Kaggle.

Target: In this projest I'm going to investigate and analyse TMDb movie dataset to explore how to evaluate a successful movie, and what is the most important factors

The data you will use for this analysis can be accessed here: "data/tmdb-movies.csv"

Required Tools¶

Library Description
numpy adding support for large, multi-dimensional arrays and matrices
pandas for data manipulation and analysis.
matplotlib & seaborn is a plotting library for data visualization

Dataset¶

the data contains about 10000 observasion, and the following columns:

  • movie_id: Integer, A unique identifier for each movie.
  • imdb_id: Char, A unique identifier for each movie on IMDB.
  • cast: List, The name of lead and supporting actors.
  • director: Char, the director of the movie
  • budget: Numeric, The budget in which the movie was made.
  • genre: List, The genre of the movie, Action, Comedy ,Thriller etc.
  • homepage: Char, A link to the homepage of the movie.
  • keywords: List, The keywords or tags related to the movie.
  • original_title: Char, The title of the movie before translation or adaptation.
  • overview: Char, A brief description of the movie.
  • popularity: Numeric, A numeric quantity specifying the movie popularity.
  • production_companies: Char, The production house of the movie.
  • release_date: Date, The date on which it was released.
  • revenue: Numeric, The worldwide revenue generated by the movie.
  • runtime: Integer, The running time of the movie in minutes.
  • tagline: Char, Movie's tagline.
  • vote_average: Numeric, average ratings the movie recieved.
  • budget_adj: Numeric, shows the budget associated movie in terms of 2010 dollars.
  • revenue_adj: Numeric, shows the revenue associated movie in terms of 2010 dollars.

Analysis Plan¶

after exploring the fields in the dataset we conduct This analysis plan which to answer the following questions.

  1. Which genres are most popular from year to year?
  2. what is the factors of high revenue ?
  3. What is the Charectistic of top movies

genre vs revenue¶

In [16]:
# Claculate number of movies for each Genre
genrecount_df = (df['genres'].str.get_dummies('|'))
data_count = genrecount_df.sum().sort_values(ascending=False)
# calculate average revenue for each genre
genre_avg_df = (df['genres'].str.get_dummies('|')).transpose() 
data_avg = (genre_avg_df * df['revenue']).transpose()
avg_revenue = data_avg.mean().sort_values(ascending=False)
# compare Genres based on number of movies made vs revenue
fig,axs=plt.subplots(ncols=2)
fig.autofmt_xdate(rotation=45)
fig.set_size_inches(16,8)
sns.barplot(x=data_count.index,y=data_count.values, ax=axs[0])
sns.barplot(x=avg_revenue.index,y=avg_revenue.values, ax=axs[1])
axs[0].set_title('Number of movies')
axs[1].set_title('Average Revenue')

plt.show()
  • Most of production companies Made Drama & Comdey types, However Action got high revenue, which means people would prefer that kind of Genre

def rate_cat(x):
    if x < 5: 
        return 'Low'
    elif x >= 5 and x <= 6: 
        return 'Medium'
    else: 
        return 'High'   
df['rate_calss'] = df['vote_average'].apply(rate_cat)
df.head()

Final Results¶

  • from the various scatter plots we can easily conclude that: The Revenue increases with increase in Popularity,That makes Revenue and Popularity are directly proportional. We also visualize the right-biased normal distributions for relationship between Revenue Vs Rating and Popularity Vs Rating.
  • from the Bar charts we can see: Drama is the most popular genre, following by action, comedy and thriller. Drame, Comedy, Thriller and Action are four most-made genres.
  • from the Pie Charts of top 20 we can conclude that: the best crew make best movies as the most successful movies Adventurer, Science-Fiction & Action, related to the Genre of the top director was Steven Spielberg whose favourit jobs in science fiction, and the top 3 actors we have (Harrison Ford, Mark Hamill, Carrie Fisher) It is worth noting that the three are related to each other, they have worked together in many roles (i.e. starwars, which is a science-fiction movie

Limitations¶

  • Firstly there were many rows within the dataframe which contained a certain amount of null values(a lot to be honest). So, first I had to DORP those rows. Furthermore, the data also contained a duplicated value row (2090), which had to be removed, following a re-check of null values for our key parameters.
  • The data in the columns of (Directors, genres, production_companies) are sperated by '|', so I needed a function which will take any column as argument from which data is need to be extracted and keep track of count takeing a given column, and separate the string by '|' .

Recommendation¶

  • i recommend to collect more information for the movies the we have not their budgect & revenue so that we can benefit from it
  • collect more data to have more accurate & usefull insights
  • search for more attribues (i.e. marketing channels details) so that we can discover how much the movie been marketed
